00:01:17.181 --> 00:01:20.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
How important is the use of illustrations?

00:01:20.601 --> 00:01:23.938 line:10% position:50% align:center
Are they simply fluff in our teaching?

00:01:23.938 --> 00:01:26.440 line:10% position:50% align:center
One definition of the English word “fluff”

00:01:26.440 --> 00:01:28.192 line:10% position:50% align:center
is this:

00:01:28.192 --> 00:01:30.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
“something essentially trivial

00:01:30.945 --> 00:01:33.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
and lacking importance or solid worth.”

00:01:34.865 --> 00:01:38.160 line:90% position:50% align:center
Are illustrations trivial
and of little worth?

00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:41.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please follow along on-screen

00:01:41.455 --> 00:01:44.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
as I read our theme scripture,

00:01:44.416 --> 00:01:46.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew 13:34:

00:01:47.795 --> 00:01:50.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
“All these things Jesus spoke to the crowds

00:01:50.673 --> 00:01:53.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
“by illustrations.

00:01:53.133 --> 00:01:55.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Indeed, without an illustration

00:01:55.135 --> 00:01:57.471 line:90% position:50% align:center
he would not speak to them.”

00:01:58.555 --> 00:02:02.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
We often call Jesus the Great Teacher.

00:02:02.101 --> 00:02:04.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
Illustrations were essential

00:02:04.478 --> 00:02:07.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
to fully grasp what was being taught.

00:02:07.731 --> 00:02:09.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, we won’t be spending a lot of time

00:02:09.942 --> 00:02:12.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the dos and don’ts of using illustrations.

00:02:13.862 --> 00:02:18.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
